00026 /// \brief
00027 /// The FdoConflictType enumeration defines conflict types required to
00028 /// identify the lock type of a conflict reported with the lock conflict reader.
00029 /// <param name="FdoConflictType_LockConflict">
00030 /// Identifies a reported conflict
00031 /// in the lock conflict reader as a lock conflict. A conflict represents a
00032 /// lock conflict if an object the user requests to be locked is already locked
00033 /// by a different user.
00034 /// </param>
00035 /// <param name="FdoConflictType_VersionConflict">
00036 /// Identifies a reported conflict
00037 /// in the lock conflict reader as a version conflict. A conflict represents a
00038 /// version conflict if an object the user requests to be locked has already been
00039 /// versioned.
00040 /// </param>
00041 /// <param name="FdoConflictType_Unsupported">
00042 /// Indicates that an unsupported or
00043 /// unknown conflict type has been encountered.
00044 /// </param>
00045 
00046 enum FdoConflictType
00047 {
00048 
00049     FdoConflictType_LockConflict,
00050     FdoConflictType_VersionConflict,
00051     FdoConflictType_Unsupported
00052 
00053 };
00054 #endif
